reviews.name: Ascension St. John Jane Phillips
reviews.full_address: 3500 SE Frank Phillips Blvd, Bartlesville, OK 74006

reviews_data.review_text: We delivered our baby boy here with Dr. Davis and felt so informed and cared for the entire time. Our nurses, Hayley, Melody, Lori and others were the kindest women ever. We felt encouraged as new partners, our baby was in safe hands. Definitely recommend this hospital and it's staff.
reviews_data.owner_answer: So glad to hear your positive feedback! Thank you for taking the time to leave us this review. Our teams are committed to delivering compassionate care in our community. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: Where should I start? Rude and lazy nurses, confused cardiologists, lack of care or communication, or Teresa that goes around pushing for DNR and hospice? My mother has been here twice due to heart failure and liver failure. First time she was placed on the cardiac floor 10 and while on meds Teresa came into her room and had my mother sign a DNR form. Teresa also came and spoke to me about the form and through the entire conversation my mom was unconscious due to her meds she was on and was trying to push me to have my mother put into hospice care. I had told her I was not ready for that yet and I wanted to see how my mom progressed. My mother was released to a rehabilitation facility for three days then ended right back at the hospital due to her meds not being given to her correctly. Then my mother was out in the CCU unit where she was kept on a dopamine drip for days. One day the Drs say she has three months at most, next day she has a year, next day from Teresa she says my mother is gonna die any day. Finally after the constant lack of communication and miscommunication from this hospital I had to tell the Drs to get their stuff straightened out and figure out what they're going to do because if they're too incompetent here then I wanted my mom transferred to Tulsa. So then it's she's getting a pacemaker so I take another day off from work to be with her, then I come in only to find out no pacemaker! The back and forth from the Drs here is enough to drive anyone crazy! Having that Teresa lady constantly harassing us for hospice care and for harassment of us deciding to reverse my mother's DNR is shocking and disgusting!! I also wrote my name and phone number on my mother's white board in every room she was in for daily phone calls and communication from the Drs or nurses, not one time did anyone bother to call me!! Only good employee we encountered is  Tamela, she is always so nice and beyond helpful. That Teresa lady should be fired!!! Cardiologist here are extremely unprofessional and beyond dumb!!!

The registration process is an absolute joke. I have never felt so pushed aside in my life. Out of the four workers we had interaction with trying to get my husband to cath lab, none of them could have cared less. They barely made any eye contact, none of them made any attempt to actually register him, and then we were asked to complete his registration ourselves on his phone. Then why are you even here? You were absolutely useless to me.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We'd appreciate the opportunity to learn more about your concern so that we can have our management team look into how we can improve. If you are willing to work with us directly, please call 918-333-7200 (Mon-Fri 8 am-4:30 pm). Thank you. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: ER staff and PA/Doctors are friendly and great. But the waiting time to be seen is ridiculous!  Two hours in the waiting room then once you go back to a room in ER it’s at least another 2 hours waiting for any testing to be completed. We have been here twice in the past 45 days for two different situations. Once the initial evaluation and routine monitors/ blood work has been done, no one comes back the room to give any updates or at least let you know you haven’t been forgotten. I realize it’s probably understaffed for the amount of people that routinely come in and it’s not the staff’s fault as they all are busy seeing other patients. It seems to us that it would be a nice touch for someone to take less than a minute to say “We haven’t forgotten about you we are just really busy, are you doing ok?”  Just our thoughts.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your review. We'd like the chance to look into the situation you have described. Could you please reach out to us at 918-333-7200 (Mon-Fri 8 am-4:30 pm). We look forward to hearing from you. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: I don't have an issue with the hospital as such but their ENT office is terrible!  My PCP has faxed over a referral 3 times to their office and no one has called me.  I call every week, am put on hold, they take down my information and tell me they will "call me right back" and never do.  I have put messages on the portal for them, even included my MRI results and no response.  The referral was due to the results of an MRI I had at the beginning of August that revealed an issue that needs attention and could become very serious if not attended to.   I am extremely frustrated as I need to get in to see them as soon as possible.  Am at a loss as to what to do except keep calling every week. Someone needs to look into their management in that office since they are part of Ascension!

The experience wS good. I just paid to much on the co pay and no one can explain why or what the charges were for. I called my ins., billing at JP and the doctors office and got the run around. So it was suggested to wait till the doctors office was through billing and go back and check everything, and if there is something wrong to act then about a possible refund. But other than that people were nice and informative. It was a nice experience with them.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you; we appreciate your feedback! We will share it with our leadership. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: My experience at your place was as pleasant as could be expected, the staff, drs, and nurses were very polite. I was very pleased about my care. My first experience for any surgery or hospital stay and can't say enough about the care I received from your knowledgeable staff thank you very much. Sincerely  Lee Davis Jr
reviews_data.owner_answer: We’re happy to hear your positive feedback! Thank you. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: My wallet and keys were stolen last friday when I was there. Security guard refused to help in anyway stating "there was nothing he could do because no one gave them to him", "Even if he saw them he couldn't get them back for me" It was a less than 30 minute time frame and he wouldn't look at their cameras or help search for them. The pain management nurse was the only helpful person. I found them dumped in the bathroom.  I hope nothing major happens at this hospital with Security Guards that have no knowledge or ability to handle situations.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We would appreciate the opportunity to work toward a resolution. Please reach out to us at 918-333-7200 (Mon-Fri 8 am-4:30 pm) at your convenience. We hope to hear from you soon. Thank you. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text:
The positive experience began with Corinne at the pre-op appointment , continued with Josefina as my prep nurse, and finished the day with all of the staff that assisted in my surgery. I can’t give enough thanks for how elk I was treated. I just feel bad that I can’t remember every name.
I’ve had a LOT of surgeries, and, unfortunately, a LOT of negative experiences. I want to extend my thanks to my surgeon, Dr Williams, and to everyone involved for exceeding the highest standard of care.
I wanted to keep my gallbladder for my lifetime, but I must have worn it out. I couldn’t have chosen better people to give it a new home - wherever that may be. 😃
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the positive review! We work hard to provide high quality care. And we are committed to delivering compassionate care to the community. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text:
I am at least grateful Mom was seen and admitted, but this was ER visit #2 on the same day.  Her Primary wanted her Admitted for “Pain Management not controlled by oral opioids.”  This was after a fall at home.  She has a fractured kneecap, and injury to her osteoporosis spine.
The fact that the Hospitalist actually did admit her to the Med/Surg floor after a few discussions with us gave me some hope that Mom would get treatment for her intractable pain.

That’s not at all what happened.  Mom was transferred to Rehabilitation the next evening. On a Friday at 4:45pm, while I was still deciding IF I WANTED HER THERE.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We would appreciate the opportunity to work with you directly regarding this review. Please know that we are dedicated to delivering compassionate care that starts with listening. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: Mostly ok. Cleaning of the room was not good. Toilet not cleaned for three days. Food service was very good. Nursing staff was also very good. When I left my prescription was sent to Walgreens and when I left it was too late to pick it up. I tried for 2 days to get it sent to my home town pharmacy with no luck. I am taking 2000 mg of Tylenol once a day to knock the edge off of the pain. It lasts about 3 hours so 21 hours of pain a day. So not a fun time.

reviews_data.review_text: The nurses and doctors are always so careful with my baby and very kind. They’ve improved so much over the years, when I was younger it wasn’t very good. I never wanted to go to this place. I always had to go all the way to Bailey’s in Owasso and I live in Bartlesville. But they’re so much better now, I’m truly amazed and thankful for everyone who works here!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Our care team aims to deliver high quality compassionate care to the community. Thanks for sharing this feedback with us! -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: ER doctor was rude and argumentative. Gave my mom narcan for idk what reason but it didn't help one bit never said what the problem with my mom was sent her home couple days later she had to get life flighted heart stopped 3 times. I feel like this could of been prevented if that doctor would have worried about my mom instead of asking questions he already knew the answers to and even answering his own questions. Absolutely ridiculous I'll never use this hospital again after ALL this!!!

reviews_data.review_text: The neurologist was great, the nursing and physical therapy staff seemed too overwhelmed to bother with care. The patient came home with bedsores, ratted dirty hair, no aftercare instructions, no in-hospital plan articulated, sores and bruises and hands and toes, and too weak for a team of professionals to help (let alone the lay care of family).
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We understand your frustration and would sincerely like to give this situation the time and attention you deserve. May we ask that you please call us at 918-333-7200 (Mon-Fri 8 am-4:30 pm) so that we can address your concerns? Thank you. 

-Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text: They missed an infection my daughter had for 3 days. Rude mental health employee . I kicked the unprofessional nurse out of my daughters room . My daughters care was very neglected I dealt with a very rude nurse that kept trying to intimidate my child by giving her dirty looks. The in house “supervisor”  wasn’t very productive on making sure my child’s medical needs were met. They were just trying to push my daughter out of there. I will be getting ahold of another supervisor at that hospital . I will in the future not go here.

Really nice team of doctors and nurses, they took great care of my husband.  The facility and grounds are kept very clean.  The cafeteria has somewhat decent food.  Nice waiting areas for families.  The ER entrance is a little hard to find, it is located all the way around, to the back of the building.

I don't understand the negative reviews. I have only ever had the very best experiences at this hospital, both as a patient and a child of a patient. Even though the nurses are overworked, they have always been extremely attentive, professional, caring and friendly toward me and my family. And the physicians on staff have also been wonderful. Might be because I always treat medical professionals with the respect and kindness they deserve so I receive that from them in return.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much, for your review! We are grateful to be in service of our communities with compassionate care. -Ascension St. John Community Manager

reviews_data.review_text:
This post has my husband's name instead of mine listed.    I am Sharolyn Brookshire. My experience was great with everyone from Dr Thompson in the emergency room to the in- patient rehab.
The nurses, all of them, my therapist  nisette, Carl, Lisa were top notch.  I can't remember all the nurses, but some were Renata, Ashley, crystal, Melinda and more, all were great and gave me the help and push I needed to leading to coming home.   I am now on my way to a complete recovery.
Thank you so much,  Sharolyn  Brookshire

reviews_data.review_text: Take the extra time and drive to Bailey's in Owasso... even if you are bleeding to death, I would take your chances and go there. I am not sure why they don't fix the issues that plague this place like extremely rude staff, severely undertrained doctors, and the secretaries. It almost seems like they wake up in a different world everyday.
